  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (da73576 2022-06-04T00:18:01.078301Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge test -w\n\n### Operating System\n\nmacOS (Apple Silicon)\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nSometimes tests disappear from the watcher.  In this example (see gif below), all I did was delete a commented line in a test contract and hit save.\r\n\r\nTest summary went from this:\r\n\r\n![Screen Shot 2022-06-04 at 9 52 05 AM](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/71567643/172017300-f55645c8-bfa0-46b2-9326-d122f0ae6ff9.png)\r\n\r\n\r\nto this:\r\n\r\n![Screen Shot 2022-06-04 at 9 53 07 AM](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/71567643/172017308-f1f68bda-3981-48d2-9a6d-c4953117c285.png)\r\n\r\nFor some reason, the watcher is now only reporting on the test contract that I just updated (by deleting a comment).\r\n\r\nIf I switch to a different test file and update.  Then the focus of the watcher goes to that new file and all other tests are ignored:\r\n\r\n![Screen Shot 2022-06-04 at 9 49 41 AM](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/71567643/172017205-fc28ecbe-f454-4890-b44e-32b77574c936.png)\r\n\r\n\r\nThe solution is to ^c and restart forge -w.\r\n\r\nSee gif below, and please let me know if there's any more helpful info I can provide.\r\n\r\n![disappearing_tests1](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/71567643/172017031-80ec019b-dbfa-4299-892d-ab740caba04b.gif)\r\n",
